content.detailedDescription: I opened the front door to let my dog out. at the end of our street is a small wooded tree area. an object came from behind the house at the end of the street. it barely flew over the trees and was clearly visible. it was a clear, cloudless night. the object appeared to be oval & made no sound at all, not even a hum. separating the two levels were long, tall, red & white alternating lights. before i saw the craft, i heard laughter coming from the trees that sounded like little kids going, "hee hee hee". as soon as the object passed over the trees, the laughing stopped. it was going very slow. the object went straight for less than 30 feet then turned to the right. when it turned it didn't turn like a plane would, dipping it wings. it just made a perfect, level turn & followed the path of the street across from my house, then slowly disappeared. the next day i saw the owners of the home outside & i said this to them, "i was just wondering if anyone heard or saw anything unusual last night." and the man said to me, "oh, if you mean the ufo's, they fly over here all the time".  although we live near an air national guard base/small airport, the object was too large to land at this airport. i know what i saw that night, and it was definitely not from this world.
content.summary: Close view of large, 2 level object at tree top level on clear night

content.detailedDescription: On november 8, 2015, tucson, az, approximately 9:00 pm, a group of gray to copper forms was observed at approximately thirty feet altitude. the forms were in a v formation and moved quickly, silently and unwaveringly from north to south. we observed for approximately ten seconds.Shapes changed from ovoid to spherical while maintaining v formation. the individual forms were approximately three feet across. at first the color was a dull gray and shifted to a reflective copper. there was a churning motion within the formation with individual spheres rotating from the outer part of the formation to the v.These were clearly not balloons or birds. the speed was rapid and constant without sound. approximately the same time that evening, there was a trident missile launch in california and people were reporting blue light sightings to the west of our city in arizona. the location of this sighting was east of the city and we were facing east looking at the stars. there was a low level of illumination, muted. the colors changed from gray to copper and also the gray outlined the spheres, within the ovoids.
content.summary: Group of 20? gray to copper spheres moved, rapidly, silently north to south. observed for 10? seconds, shape change occured from ovoid to spherical, maintaining v-formation. spheres moved individually, but appeared to be connected somehow.

content.detailedDescription:
Some time in 1995 my girlfriend and i got into my car, which was parked in front of my parents house. the car was facing south, and there was a clear view of the sky facing the direction. there are trees that line the east and west sides of the street, but the view is unobstructed to the south. it was very dark on the street with no street lights present. my girlfriend turned on the interior light to pull a cd out of the case, and as i was waiting i noticed a bright light coming over the trees at the end of the road, which were a little less than a quarter mile to the south. as i was watching the light, it changed from moving in a straight path to a zig zag. it wasn't moving very fast and i thought it was a helicopter. what first really piqued my interest was the abruptness that the object made each change of direction as it zig sagged. it didn't make a sort of circular arc as you'd expect a helicopter to make as it changed direction, they were very sudden movements from ne to nw and back again. at this point i told my girlfriend to look at the object. she agreed that it was unusual. when the object was about 45 to 50 in viewing angle to the south, it stopped all movement. i couldn't see any shape or even determine how high or far away it was, just that the light it was giving off was much brighter than any of the stars or planets viewable that night. the object remained stationary for about one minute, and then began moving at the same speed as before. it travelled 20 degrees to the wnw and stopped again. it remained stationary for about 20 seconds and took off from that position at a speed that literally took my breath away. it covered about 50 degrees of sky in about 1 second and my view was obstructed by trees and my parent's house.
there were two navy bases within 15 miles of my parent's house, and i grew up seeing military aircraft on a daily basis.  nothing i have every seen moved with the speed that this object did at the end of my observation. the object appeared to be at a fairly high elevation for the duration that i viewed it, but even if it were 1000 ft high, the speed that it moved at the end would have been incredible. the point being that words really don't properly convey how absolutely amazing watching this object move across the sky was.
  i should also say that i am a staunch skeptic of all things paranormal,  and if i hadn't seen this myself i'm not sure that i would've believed someone if they described this event with no real corroborating evidence besides a second witness, but i know what i saw and it changed me in some way. i don't think that the technology to make a craft, or whatever it was, accelerate from a stop to those speeds will be available in our lifetime. but suspending disbelief and assuming it was possible, i know without a doubt that a human being inside of it would have no chance whatsoever of surviving that type of acceleration.
  thank you for taking the time to evaluate this experience that i had. also, i didn't include my girlfriend's reactions to this event because i didn't want to speak for her, but suffice it to say she was as astonished by what we witnessed as much as i was. 

thank you again,
scott brandle
content.flightPath: Stationary,Path with directional change,Path then hovering
content.summary: Object moved from south in zig zag pattern, came to a stop. moved 70 degrees across sky in less than 2 seconds and was gone from sight.

content.detailedDescription:
On nov 19, 2015 i went outside in my backyard when i noticed that the chemtrails( s to n in w sky) drifting upwards like a fan. it looked interesting so i decided to go grab my phone and take a picture. i sent it to my son via text and took another look at the picture and noticed something bright blue. 
it was hardly noticeable but it caught my eye and took a closer look.   
i zoomed in on it and i can clearly see a cluster of bluish green lights. i immediately text my son about what i saw. he replied, saying that he noticed it but thought it was coming from his phone screen. 
i forwarded the image to my ipad, to view the image on a larger screen. it definitely has a bell shaped, or triangular/pyramid shape. the image can be enhanced with a filter, black and white is striking. i took more pics of the sky right away but the object had disappeared. i have many pics on my phone, i have never had any unusual spots or flares on any saved images prior or after this day.
 i do want to note that i did not see it with my own two eyes before or while taking the pic of the chemtrails. it was only after taking it that i seen the ufo. i do not believe it is an artifact. i am 100% sure i captured something from another world or dimension, if it was by accident or intentional , i cannot explain how or why but you decide. thanks.

content.detailedDescription:
i work nights and i was on my deck at about 2 am. the sky was clear, stars were present and little to no clouds. 

i saw this phenomenon over burlington twp  on 11/17/15 at 2:30 am.

after a falling flash of green light ,there appeared  6 orbs travelling north between the de river and rt 130.  

i thought maybe birds at first but then quickly dismissed that notion when the orbs began to perform.  they were in a straight line formation, then changed to a v. then they split to 3 and 3. the center 2 orbs flew in sync while the others flew alternating patterns of circles, figure eights and colliding semicircles around them. it was an awesome display!﻿

i am absolutely certain of what i witnessed. it took about 90 seconds for this all to happen before i lost view over the horizon.  

then i began to think who else could have seen it. 

anybody travelling on the burlington bristol bridge or pa turnpike bridge in florence would have had the highest vantage point. 

then i checked your site and noticed that somebody saw something similar to what i saw in va earlier, and even before that in the carolinas.

maybe somebody else will report it further north.

i have always believed but this was my first encounter.
content.summary: I saw this phenomenon over burlington twp  on 11/17/15 at 2:30 am. after a falling flash of green light ,there appeared  6 orbs travelling north between the de river and rt 130.  they were in a straight line formation, then changed to a v. then they split

content.detailedDescription:
I left for work and traveling 30 mph down a wooded road when i saw a large aircraft above the treetops to my right side of my truck to in front of me moving slow motion. a few cars in front of me at a short distance and no one behind me. i should have pulled over & took a picture with my cell phone! 

the last time in my life i saw something of the magnitude & shape was a stealth craft in s.A. during desert storm!

what caught my attention with alarm was it was quite unusual to see so many lights outlining the wing structure- maybe like a boomerang shape with a solid center because that's the area i saw a red pulse-like flashing light-similar to what you'd see on our airplanes. the white lights were bright not dull.

that morning before i left my house already felt quiet, a bit strange, unsettling so to speak.

the 1st thing i thought to myself was "what the hell is that!" i was waiting for a beam of light to appear then i would have panicked. at a glance i thought it was an airplane flying low towards bwi but our planes don't have wings lined with white lights. our planes have lights on wing-tips. i did see a red pulsed light underbelly as one would see on an aircraft but again, our planes have a few not just one.

the weather was drizzling lightly but visibility was clear, no fog ~a craft flying that low would be loud and produce noise-sound waves, i heard none. no other objects or crafts seen. i see air traffic- normal planes all the time. this was certainly different.

last night my oldest daughter, kimberly robeson said she too witnessed a similar situation the night before and too, filed this info with mufon.

the question i have is who does one call in a situation  like this? abnormal craft that look of an unknown origin? it's frightening! what do you do?

i have always been level-headed, well ground, alert and oriented healthcare professional. weird stuff doesn't come to me that often. but this left me a bit shaken inside. i am a believer too, that we are not alone in this universe. we are fools to believe otherwise~~
content.summary: Low flying craft shaped like a plane but not a plane size larger than 747 approx

content.detailedDescription: We had just come home and we were unloading groceries. as usual i was staring up into the sky looking over the tree line towards lake huron. i live five minutes from the lake on foot, so very near. above the  tree line from the south appeared a very, very bright streak followed immediately by other one. they were almost attached. my first thought was it was the iss but it was way to low and fast for any craft.  it was present just long enough for me to yell look to the others and i started running north to track it. i believe it headed northeast out over lake huron or stayed near the shoreline.  i would describe this light as a very long rectangle/streak with form with a very small crack then another identical long rectangle/streak with form. they were very, very bright orange/yellow. they were thin but large and long enough to take up at least one half of my sky vision at first appearance. i would also compare them to snow skis and how they move through the snow hard, fast and strong while being close together.
content.summary: Standing in my driveway looking over the trees towards lake huron. above the tree line i spot two very bright streaks, one quickly tracking the other with a small break. moved very quick.

content.detailedDescription:
Saturday night, november 14th, 2015 at 6:16pm pst i returned home from shopping. home is just east of corona, ca. it was very clear out that night so before going inside i decided to scan the skies for any activity. this was something i've been in the habit of doing many times a week since november of 2011 when i had my first ufo sighting. i've had quite a few over the past 4 years. never the same object, different hours of the day and both day and night, all of them from the driveway of my home. i'm convinced beyond a reasonable doubt that this area, for whatever reason, is a ufo hotspot.
 standing in my driveway facing north i was looking up and slightly east in the area surrounding the cassiopeia constellation. there always seems to be activity in that general area. but even knowing this i wasn't expecting what came next.
  from the east came a v formation of light green, sort of flourecent, lights. one leading, with two on the south side, and three on the north. the last of the three on the north side was slightly trailing the others throwing the formation off a bit. they were flying at a moderately fast pace from east to west and i was able to get a good look at them for probably four seconds. being that they weren't brightly lit i lost them in the darkness as opposed to them flying behind an obstruction. there was also a moment where my brain was trying to convince me that what i was seeing was a flock of birds. this thought kicked in as soon as i percieved no sound from the group as they passed overhead. but i dismissed that notion quickly as i recalled the rounded off arrowhead shape of the matching crafts and the distance that they covered in the four seconds. i figured it was probably close to two miles which converts to approximately 1800 mph. unfortunately, i had no reference to help me determine their correct altitude. but the v formation was probably slightly smaller than my palm when i extend my arm. i do believe they were flying in our atmosphere, rather than distant space.
 i immediately noted the time of the sighting. i stayed outside for a few more minutes before going inside and checking the internet for similar sightings. but as of right now, 5 days later, no matches. i'm hoping that someone who may have experienced these same crafts will feel more inclined to share their experience if they see someone has posted before them. many times, fear of ridicule is an unfortunate by-product of these types of experiences. post your experience, everyone. it's important that you do so.
content.summary: Six rounded arrowhead-shaped craft flying in v formation over so california. light green flourecent in color. silent.

content.detailedDescription: I was outside the cedar park cinemark watching the leonid meteor shower at exactly 10:25pm when i witnessed a shooting star travel across the sky leaving a trail and flash, not more than 20 seconds later i witnessed a formation of 4 small white lights in a triangular formation appear abruptly traveling slowly in a south easterly direction. the formation was a three pointed triangle with a white light in the center. all of the lights were of the same color, size and intensity. all four of the lights we're moving in an indistinct pattern changing shape while remaining clustered. halfway through the observable flight path the entire formation  changed direction very distinctly at almost a 35 degree angle and resumed a flight pattern to the east before fading into the distance well above the horizon. this is the first time i have ever seen anything like this and i don't know how to explain it but as an experienced star gazer i guarantee this was no shooting star or man-made craft. there was no cloud cover and the craft was completely silent. i would estimate the altitude at around 8,000 feet.
content.summary: 5 small white lights moving at speed in formation changing shape with one directional change

content.detailedDescription:
I and my friend ellen were walking to church on an overcast saturday evening in september 1977.  not sure of the exact date or time anymore, but it was an overcast evening, a slight chill in the air, and it was still light out.  we had only walked one block from ellen's house and were still on woodruff ave, iselin, nj when the huge pine trees on the property to the right of us suddenly started waving and causing a huge wind sound due to a sudden wind.  it caught our attention, and we both looked up to see what might have been causing the sudden wind.....At this time, we both  looked
 directly upwards, and we saw a huge grayish completely round object descending from the grayish cloud cover.... it remained below the cloud cover for at least 15 seconds at which point we both started running away ....Ellen and i witnessed this and we both took off running to our friend dee's house... two blocks away.  when we got there, we told her mother what had just happened...And her mother accompanied us as we ran back the two blocks to where it had happened...When we arrived there was nothing to see.  they were gone.
content.summary: Huge round ufo descended from the clouds; hung above me and my friend for a minute or two.. we panicked and ran to our friends house...When we returned with our friends mother, it was gone

content.detailedDescription:
As i was coming home from work and turned the corner into my subdivision, i saw what i thought was a street light, that has been out for a few days, trying to start. i noticed it was moving, however. i stopped my vehicle, rolled down the driver-side window, and turned off the radio. the object appeared to be round, or spherical, in shape. it didn't really have a shape, but was merely a ball of bright orange light with no distinct shape, somewhat like looking at a flare. it seemed to be brighter in the center, more whitish. there was no noise and the motion was in a straight line - approximately north to south. because the speed seemed similar to an airplane on approach to an airport, i thought maybe it was a plane with an engine fire, but, again, no noise. not knowing what it was or how big it was, it would be difficult to estimate its altitude, but it did not seem to be very high. i eventually lost sight of it as some houses blocked my view. the entire observation lasted for approximately two minutes, or so.

having followed ufo reports for many years, this object was nothing like anything i've ever read about or seen in pictures.
content.summary: Fireball-like bright orange round/spherical object moving from north to south

content.detailedDescription:
I was sitting outside when i suddenly noticed something that looked like the trace of meteroid, but it didn't fade...And it was moving. dead perfectly straight, very thin, about the length of my index finger held at arm's length. like a huge sewing needle. its direction of travel was inclined about 10 degrees to its long axis, traveling due north. sort of like it was tacking instead of traveling along its axis.  it did not flutter, rotate, change velocity or brightness. it took about 20 seconds to travel from overhead to behind the trees.

as an astronomy enthusiast, i've seen lots of meteroids, comets, contrails lit by moonlight, satellites, debris thrown up by wind, even flocks of geese with their bellies lit up by city lights. this looked nothing like any of those. 

pretty sure this was terrestrial, but i can't come up with a possible object.
